      "rationale": "Testing was performed at a single load rate (5 mm/min) and single temperature (23 ± 2 °C) per ASTM F1717. The COU encompasses only room-temperature quasi-static loading, so temperature variation is not a gap. However, only one load rate was evaluated; rate sensitivity was not characterized. Achieved level 2 is below required level 3 — this is a documented gap accepted by the credibility assessment team given the quasi-static nature of the application and supporting literature showing negligible rate sensitivity for metallic constructs in this regime."
